                        "steps":  [
                                      "Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil for the pasta. Cook the pasta until al dente, then reserve 1 cup pasta water before draining.",
                                      "While the pasta cooks, pat the chicken cutlets dry. If any pieces are thicker than about 1/4 inch, pound them thinner so they cook quickly and evenly.",
                                      "Season the chicken with salt and pepper. Put the flour in a shallow bowl, lightly coat each cutlet, and shake off the excess so the coating is thin, not cakey.",
                                      "Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. When the butter foams, add chicken in a single layer without crowding.",
                                      "Sear the chicken in batches for about 2 to 3 minutes per side, until golden and just cooked through. Move cooked pieces to a plate and add a little more oil if the pan gets dry.",
                                      "Lower the heat to medium. Add the garlic and stir for about 30 seconds, just until fragrant. Add the wine if using, scraping up browned bits, and simmer for 1 minute; otherwise go straight to chicken broth.",
                                      "Add chicken broth, lemon juice, and capers. Simmer for 3 to 5 minutes, until the sauce reduces slightly and tastes bright but not harsh.",
                                      "Lower the heat and whisk in the remaining butter a piece at a time until the sauce looks glossy. If serving with pasta and the sauce looks too tight, loosen it with a splash of reserved pasta water.",
                                      "Return the chicken to the skillet and spoon sauce over it for 1 to 2 minutes. Keep a few cutlets plain or lightly sauced if needed for kids.",
                                      "Toss the pasta with some of the sauce, or serve pasta plain with chicken and sauce on top. Finish with parsley if using and serve with extra sauce and capers on the side."
                                  ],
